'''Minardil''', {{TA|1454}}<ref name="Elendil">{{PM|Elendil}}, manuscript C, The Southern Line of Gondor: the Anarioni, 25. Minardil</ref> - {{TA|1634|n}},<ref>{{App|South}}, ''Kings of Gondor'', Minardil, p. 1038</ref> was the twenty-fifth [[King of Gondor]].<ref>{{App|South}}, ''Kings of Gondor'', p. 1038</ref>

==History==
Minardil ascended the throne after the death of his father [[Hyarmendacil II]] in {{TA|1621}}<ref>{{App|South}}, ''Kings of Gondor'', Hyarmendacil II (Vinyarion), p. 1038</ref> who had defeated the Men of Harad in {{TA|1551}}.<ref>{{App|TA}}, entry for the year 1551, p. 1086</ref>

Since the end of the [[Kin-strife]], when the sons of [[Castamir|Castamir the Usurper]] escaped to [[Umbar]], the rebels in Umbar had made war upon [[Gondor]], raiding its coast and assailing its ships for generations.<ref>{{App|Gondor}}, entry for king Eldacar, p. 1047</ref>

In {{TA|1634}},<ref>{{App|TA}}, entry for the year 1634, p. 1086</ref> Minardil was killed in [[Pelargir]] by the [[Corsairs of Umbar]] who were led by the great-grandsons of [[Castamir]], [[Angamaitë]] and [[Sangahyando]].<ref>{{App|Gondor}}, entry for king Minardil, p. 1048</ref>

During Minardil's brief reign his Steward was [[Húrin of Emyn Arnen]]. After Minardil's reign the kings of Gondor always chose their stewards from among Húrin's descendants, and eventually the Stewardship would become hereditary within the [[House of Húrin]].<ref>{{App|Stewards}}, first paragraph, p. 1052</ref>

==Etymology==
''Minardil'' is a [[Quenya]] name. Its meaning is not glossed, but Paul Strack suggests that it means "Friend of the Tower" and is a compound of a shortened form ''minas'' of [[minasse]] ("tower") and [[-ndil|-(n)dil]] ("friend").<ref>{{webcite|author=Paul Strack|articleurl=https://www.eldamo.org/content/words/word-2435487965.html|articlename=Q. ''Minardil'' m.|website=Eldamo|accessed=28 July 2021}}</ref>

